{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idaa03003b-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3015"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3015"},"text":"§ 3015.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Simplified acquisition threshold","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"In this part:","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa03003c-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3015/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “simplified acquisition threshold” has the meaning provided that term in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t41/s134"},"text":"section 134 of title 41","children":[],"tail":", except that, in the case of any contract to be awarded and performed, or purchase to be made, outside the United States in support of a contingency operation or a humanitarian or peacekeeping operation, the term means an amount equal to two times the amount specified for that term in such section."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"idaa03003d-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s3015/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The term “humanitarian or peacekeeping operation” means a military operation in support of the provision of humanitarian or foreign disaster assistance or in support of a peacekeeping operation under chapter VI or VII of the Charter of the United Nations. The term does not include routine training, force rotation, or stationing.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idaa03003e-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(Added and amended ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/dA/tXVIII/s1806/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, div. A, title XVIII, § 1806(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", (6), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2021-01-01"},"text":"Jan. 1, 2021","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/134/4153"},"text":"134 Stat. 4153","children":[],"tail":", 4154.)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idaa03003f-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idaa030040-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"idaa030041-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The text of pars. (7) and (8) of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s2302"},"text":"section 2302 of this title","children":[],"tail":", which were transferred to this section, redesignated as pars. (1) and (2), respectively, and amended by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/283/s1806/b/6"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–283, § 1806(b)(6)","children":[],"tail":", was based on "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/355/tI/s1502"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–355, title I, § 1502","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-10-13"},"text":"Oct. 13, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/3296"},"text":"108 Stat. 3296","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/201/dA/tVIII/s807/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–201, div. A, title VIII, § 807(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-09-23"},"text":"Sept. 23, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/2606"},"text":"110 Stat. 2606","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"